COMPONENT NAME: IKM SQL to File Append
AUTHOR: Oracle
Description : - Integration Knowledge Module - Optionally Integrates column headers into the flat (Delimited format) file. - The file is populated in truncate / insert mode.
Restrictions: - All target file columns have to be defined as 'string' - Each target file column length have to be larger than the related column name - TRUNCATE option when set to true creates the file if it does not exist and truncates the file if it exists - Target file must be physically accessible by ODI Agent - No transformation can be performed on the Target.
Check this option if you wish to remove the target datastore. This option must be used with create target table option.
Check this option if you wish to create the target file. Will error out if file already exists.
Check this option to create the file if it does not exist and truncate the file if it exists.
Check this option if you wish to insert a header row into the target file that lists the names of the columns.
Automatically attempts to insert data into the Target Datastore of the Interface
